        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 8 at 3:57AM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 357 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of Beloit, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Asherville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
